  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A randomised controlled trial of Lichen Sclerosus in a period of six months measuring Quality
      of Life and sexuality among women with Lichen Sclerosus.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The patients are randomized to an intervention Group and a control Group. The intervention
      gets 6-8 visits with clinical sexologist and the control Group is having the usual care.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
